{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"aac5d943-e2f2-4d84-85ea-7fbce67be19f","content":"Here's what I found:\n\n**`my_app/views.py:3`** — `datetime.now()` hard-coded in the view.\n\n```\nnow = datetime.now()\n```\n\n### Why it's untestable\n\nCalling `datetime.now()` directly couples your code to the system clock. You can't freeze or control time in tests without monkeypatching.\n\n### Recommended fix\n\nUse Django's `timezone.now()` (timezone-aware) and inject it via a default argument or use [`freezegun`](https://github.com/spulec/freezegun) in tests:\n\n```python\nfrom django.utils import timezone\n\ndef index(request):\n    now = timezone.now()\n    return render(request, 'index.html', {'time': now})\n```\n\nThis is a small project with only **1 file** and **1 occurrence**. The fix is straightforward — want me to apply it?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"47185f30-81eb-42e5-ab6d-b7df97eca7b7","outputTokens":218,"requestId":"5C21:31910B:39EAD2:4929B7:69F561DC"},"id":"64d69ea5-0c42-4c1f-96d5-8cbc5c76b926","timestamp":"2026-05-02T02:30:57.743Z","parentId":"4f57fa4a-3828-445e-9feb-75b7fbf41064"}
